cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about training neural probabilistic language models, which is a topic that falls under the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of noise-contrastive estimation, which is a machine learning technique, so it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of language models for sentence completion, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it is a task related to understanding and generating natural language descriptions of visual content.
